>",["^57",["heightType","auto","horizontalAlign","left","hidden",false,"imageWidth","fit","margin","4px 8px","showInEditor",false,"verticalAlign","center","tooltipText","","value","Decision Log Introduction & FAQ","style",["^57",["fontSize","30px","fontWeight","700","fontFamily","Saans"]],"disableMarkdown",false,"overflowType","scroll","maintainSpaceWhenHidden",false]],"^5?",["^57",[]],"^5@",["^0",["^ ","n","position2","v",["^ ","^59","grid","^5D","","^5J","header","^5K","modalFrameDecisionLogInfo","row",0,"col",0,"^5L",0.6,"^5M",9,"^5N",0,"^5O",null]]],"^5A",null,"^5B",null,"^5C",null,"^5D","","^7","~m1731433301370","^5E","~m1731433637893","^5F","","^5G","decisions","^5H",null,"^5I",null]]],"modalCloseButton29",["^0",["^ ","n","pluginTemplate","v",["^ ","id","modalCloseButton29","^58","2d3b4d2c-ced6-4552-8693-8638b2a1e442","^59","widget","^5:","ButtonWidget2","^5;",null,"^5<",null,"^5=",null,"^5>",["^57",["heightType","fixed","horizontalAlign","right","clickable",false,"iconAfter","","submitTargetId",null,"hidden",false,"ariaLabel","Close","text","","margin","4px 8px","showInEditor",false,"tooltipText","","style",["^57",["border","transparent"]],"allowWrap",true,"styleVariant","outline","submit",false,"iconBefore","bold/interface-delete-1","events",["^D",[["^57",["event","click","type","widget","method","setHidden","pluginId","modalFrameDecisionLogInfo","params",["^57",["hidden",true]],"waitType","debounce","waitMs","0"]]]],"loading",false,"loaderPosition","auto","disabled",false,"maintainSpaceWhenHidden",false]],"^5?",["^57",[]],"^5@",["^0",["^ ","n","position2","v",["^ ","^59","grid","^5D","","^5J","header","^5K","modalFrameDecisionLogInfo","row",0,"col",10,"^5L",1.2,"^5M",2,"^5N",0,"^5O",null]]],"^5A",null,"^5B",null,"^5C",null,"^5D","","^7","~m1731433301432","^5E","~m1731433563346","^5F","","^5G","decisions","^5H",null,"^5I",null]]],"text225",["^0",["^ ","n","pluginTemplate","v",["^ ","id","text225","^58","2392a09d-0627-44cf-b854-a385089adc36","^59","widget","^5:","TextWidget2","^5;",null,"^5<",null,"^5=",null,"^5>",["^57",["heightType","auto","horizontalAlign","left","hidden",false,"imageWidth","fit","margin","4px 8px","showInEditor",false,"verticalAlign","center","tooltipText","","value","## What is it?

The Decision Log is a central repository for big decisions we make at Retool. It will include details on decisions that were made, who was involved in the decision-making process, and the rationale for the decision. It will become more populated over time as more big decisions are made.

## Why did we build it?

We want to empower all Retools to understand how we make big decisions. As the company grows, the list of decisions we make will grow as well. While we’ll continue to highlight big decisions in other forums (including in company All Hands, departmental All Hands, company-wide emails and Slack announcements, etc.), maintaining a central decision repository will make it easier for anyone to find and revisit these decisions in detail. 

We also want to ensure that decisions are made in a consistent way across the company. The Decision Log will encourage use of [a standard decision-making template](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1_e0k0Yr0_p3lV1wiqJWIIzHIL71yjICuXaQysAdudH4/edit?tab=t.0) and [the RAPID framework](https://retoolconfluence.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/BIZOPS/pages/698613862/RAPID+Retool+s+Decision-Making+Framework).

## What kinds of decisions will be added to the Decision Log?

We’d ultimately like to follow the same guidelines that we do for [when you should build a RAPID](https://retoolconfluence.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/BIZOPS/pages/698613862/RAPID+Retool+s+Decision-Making+Framework#When-should-I-build-a-RAPID%3F). Specifically, if:

* You’re responsible for getting to a decision (or have made a decision)  
* The decision isn’t part of an established, ongoing process (for example, the established process for deciding what features will be included in the next stable release)  
* The decision impacts teams beyond your own

…then you should consider adding it to the Decision Log\!

To start, the staff team will add big decisions that they make to the log.

## Who can add a decision to the Decision Log?

All Retools have the ability to log a decision. While the staff team will add big decisions that they make to the log, others are encouraged (but not required at this time) to add their own if they meet the criteria above. The more decisions we add to the log, the more valuable it will become.

## When should I add a decision to the Decision Log?

The best time to add a decision to the log is right when you start the process of making it. Note that you can choose to hide the decision until it’s ready for public consumption, or to make it visible that a decision is “in process” without sharing the related documentation until it’s ready.

When you click “Log a decision” and fill in the requisite fields, it will populate a Google Doc for you to fill in with more information about the decision. Our hope is that \- for most decisions \- you use this template from the start to guide the decision-making process (even if it won’t be visible to the company until the decision is finalized).

If you’ve already made a decision or already have a doc, that’s ok too \- you can log it at any time.

## What best practices should I consider when making and logging a decision?

At Retool, we follow [the RAPID decision-making framework](https://retoolconfluence.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/BIZOPS/pages/698613862/RAPID+Retool+s+Decision-Making+Framework) for all big, cross-functional decisions. Per those guidelines, all decisions should follow a common process:

1. Surface the need for a decision and identify the owners  
   1. Someone surfaces a decision that needs to be made and identifies the **D**. If the **D** agrees that a decision/process is required, they identify the **R** who will be responsible for writing the proposal. (In some cases, these may all be the same person).  
2. Agree on path forward and RAPID stakeholders  
   1. The **R** and **D** break the decision down into its components (if relevant) and lay out timelines and RAPIDs for each component. RAPID stakeholders are notified.  
   2. **This is when the R should log the decision and create a doc** (though you may not share the decision with the company yet).  
3. Get input and make recommendations  
   1. The **R** works with **I**s and **A**s to collect all relevant facts and perspectives, then synthesizes results and formulates recommendations. If any **A**s disagree with a recommendation, there may be some iteration before the final decision. **P**s may also be given a heads-up at this stage to prepare for execution.  
4. Decide and communicate  
   1. **D** makes the final decision based on the recommendation(s). If required, **D** also resolves any outstanding disputes between **R** and **A**s. **D** is responsible for communicating the decision to all stakeholders (though they may enlist the **R** to create and/or execute the comms plan).  
   2. **This is when the decision should be made publicly visible in the decision log** (if it isn’t already).  
5. Execute  
